<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>🐱 Kitten World - Home</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>
  <nav>
    <div class="nav-container">
      <a href="index.html" class="logo">🐱 Kitten World</a>
      <ul class="nav-links">
        <li><a href="index.html" class="active">Home</a></li>
        <li><a href="about.html">About Kittens</a></li>
        <li><a href="gallery.html">Gallery</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <section class="hero">
    <h1>Welcome to Kitten World! 🐾</h1>
    <p>Your ultimate destination for everything adorable about kittens. Learn, explore, and fall in love with these tiny bundles of joy.</p>
  </section>

  <main class="container">
    <div class="section-header">
      <h2>Why We Love Kittens</h2>
      <p>Discover what makes these little furballs so special</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card-grid">
      <div class="card">
        <h3>💤 They Sleep a LOT</h3>
        <p>Kittens can sleep up to 20 hours a day! This is because growing takes a lot of energy, and sleep helps their bodies develop properly.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>👀 Blue Eyes at Birth</h3>
        <p>All kittens are born with blue eyes! Their true eye color develops over the first few months of life. What color will yours be?</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>🍼 Rapid Growth</h3>
        <p>Kittens grow incredibly fast - they double their weight in the first week! By 6 months, they're about half their adult size.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="margin-top: 3rem;">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>Quick Facts</h2>
        <p>Impress your friends with kitten knowledge!</p>
      </div>
      <ul class="facts-list">
        <li>🐾 Kittens start walking at around 3 weeks old</li>
        <li>🥛 They begin eating solid food at 4-5 weeks</li>
        <li>🎵 They can purr from just a few days old</li>
        <li>🧶 The word "kitten" comes from Middle English "kitoun"</li>
        <li>🏠 A group of kittens is called a "kindle"</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div style="text-align: center; margin-top: 3rem;">
      <a href="gallery.html" class="btn" style="background: var(--primary); color: white; padding: 1rem 2rem; border-radius: 30px; text-decoration: none; display: inline-block;">See Cute Kittens →</a>
    </div>
  </main>

  <footer>
    <p>Made with ❤️ for kitten lovers everywhere</p>
  </footer>

  <script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
